==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sweven
<hw>Swe"ven</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[AS. <ets>swefen</ets>
sleep, dream; akin to <ets>swebban</ets>, <ets>swefian</ets>, to put to
sleep, to kill. ⟦root⟧176. See <er>Somnolent</er>.]</ety> <def>A vision
seen in sleep; a dream.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Wycliff (Acts
ii. 17).</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I defy both <qex>sweven</qex> and dream.</q>
<rj><qau>Chaucer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Swich</ent>⟦br⟧
